FAQs
What are the basic requirements to study medicine in Malaysia?
The basic requirements include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, language proficiency (usually in English), and passing the entrance exam specific to the university.

Is studying medicine in Malaysia expensive?
Tuition fees and living expenses in Malaysia are generally lower compared to Western countries. Scholarships and financial aid can also help reduce costs.

How can I apply for scholarships to study in Malaysia?
You can apply for scholarships through the universities, as well as through Malaysian government programs and private organizations. Qadri-International can assist you in finding and applying for suitable scholarships.

Are degrees from Malaysian medical universities recognized worldwide?
Yes, degrees from Malaysian medical universities are widely recognized and respected globally. Graduates often have the qualifications needed to practice medicine in various countries around the world.

